  <recipe>
    <head>
      <title>Banana Pudding</title>
      <categories>
        <cat>All newly t</cat>
        <cat>Dessert</cat></categories>
      <yield>1</yield></head>
    <ingredients>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit/></amt>
        <item>Box (4 serv size) instant vanilla pudding</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit>can</unit></amt>
        <item>Sweetened condensed milk</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1 1/2</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>Water</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>2</qty>
          <unit/></amt>
        <item>Cartons (8 oz) whipping cream</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>4</qty>
          <unit/></amt>
        <item>Bananas, sliced</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>40</qty>
          <unit/></amt>
        <item>Vanilla wafers</item></ing></ingredients>
    <directions>
      <step>  Mix together condensed milk, water and pudding mix.
  
  Chill 5 minutes. Whip cream until stiff and fold into pudding mixture.
  
  Layer pudding mixture, sliced bananas and vanilla wafers, ending with
  pudding layer.
  
  Crush some of vanilla wafers and sprinkle on top.
  
  Chill and serve.
  
